# Generate and show the demo video

When you change this repository in a way that affects the TUI or demo flow,
treat the demo video as part of the deliverable—not optional follow-up work.

## When to regenerate

Regenerate `demo/diff-tool-python-demo.mp4` in the **same change** when you modify:

- User-visible TUI behavior (panels, title bar, diff view, browser, status bar)
- Key bindings, mouse handling, or CLI arguments that the demo exercises
- Demo assets (`demo/*.tape`, `demo/*.py`, overlay timing in `key-hints.ass`)
- Anything that would make the checked-in demo video stale or misleading

Skip regeneration only for purely internal changes with zero visual impact.

## How to regenerate

1. Build the release binary: `pixi run build`
2. Record and post-process: `pixi run demo-video`
   - Runs VHS on `demo/diff-demo.tape`
   - Burns in subtitles from `demo/key-hints.ass` via `ffmpeg`
3. Commit the updated `demo/diff-tool-python-demo.mp4` with the code change.

If the change introduces new UI behavior worth highlighting, update
`demo/diff-demo.tape` and/or `demo/key-hints.ass` so the recording shows it.

## Show the video to the user

After regenerating (or when the user asks to see the demo), embed the local
file in your final response:

```html
<video src="/workspace/demo/diff-tool-python-demo.mp4" controls playsinline width="900"></video>
```

Also mention that README.md embeds the same file from the repo root path
`demo/diff-tool-python-demo.mp4`.

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] `pixi run build` succeeded
- [ ] `pixi run demo-video` succeeded
- [ ] `demo/diff-tool-python-demo.mp4` committed when regenerated
- [ ] Demo video embedded in the agent response when user-visible UI changed
